parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause electrical fires, engine stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke or fire from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine fires, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: white smoke from the exhaust pipe

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause equipment failure, engine stalling, and potentially lead to engine fires, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Cracking or brittleness of the wiring insulation

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unexplained engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs in heavy traffic or at high speeds.

The sudden and unexpected acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, especially when slowing down or approaching a stop, as it can cause the vehicle to lurch forward unexpectedly, potentially resulting in loss of control or collision.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates forward when applying pressure to the brake pedal
especially when slowing down for a stop light
requiring the driver to press harder on the brake pedal to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control or accidents, especially on highways or high-speed roads.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to function properly
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly.
